<subSubSection pageId="188" pageNumber="189" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="188.[151,1436,1183,1354]" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">
This family of predominantly Neotropical acalyptrate flies contains 177 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." box="[1062,1230,1219,1246]" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" refId="ref358584" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2012) Flies. The natural history and diversity of Diptera. Firefly Books, Richmond Hill, 616 pp." type="book" year="2012">Marshall 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." pageId="188" pageNumber="189" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[233,425,1255,1282]" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b)</bibRefCitation>
described two species from South America, considered as valid, in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Steyskal 1968 c)" baseAuthorityName="Steyskal" baseAuthorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Richardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1325,1436,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">Richardia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[159,336,1291,1318]" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref375309" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1968 c) Family Richardiidae. In: Papavero, N. (Ed.), A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States. Departamento de Zoologia, Secretaria de Agricultura, Sao Paulo, 53, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="1968">Steyskal 1968c</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1848" box="[594,837,1291,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Richardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unifasciata">
<emphasis box="[594,837,1291,1318]" italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">Richardia unifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has presumably been lost; the 
<typeStatus box="[1188,1286,1291,1317]" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Richardiidae" genus="Richardia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="188" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laterina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="188" pageNumber="189">Richardia laterina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the MZUN.
</paragraph>
